      "message": "So, I\u0027m still a bit torn on using \u0027direct\u0027 backend here, because we should strive to use \u0027libvirt\u0027 backend.\n\nA bit of background: \n\nAs we know there are two libguestfs backends: (a) \u0027direct\u0027, which makes libguestfs to directly use QEMU to launch its appliance and; (B) \u0027libvirt\u0027, which makes libguestfs use libvirt.\n\nWe should prefer to use \u0027libvirt\u0027 backend whenever possible, *unless* you are trying to workaround bugs in libvirt, in which case you can use \u0027direct\u0027 backend.  This is also what the libguestfs maintainers suggest.\n\n[*] http://libguestfs.org/guestfs.3.html#backend",
